    {
      "title": "Calculate the ratio a/b",
      "content": "Using $a = 22.41(b + c)$:<br/>$$\\frac{a}{b} = 22.41 \\cdot \\frac{b + c}{b} = 22.41 \\cdot \\frac{1.83}{0.83}$$<br/>Compute: $22.41 \\times 1.83 = 41.0103$, then $41.0103 \\div 0.83 = 49.41$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Convert to a percentage",
      "content": "$$\\frac{a}{b} \\times 100\\% = 49.41 \\times 100\\% = 4941\\%$$<br/>That matches choice D \u2014 <strong>D</strong> is correct."
